Description: Franklin Haney (FLH) Company is a financial company that invests in property development and real estate.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: Franklin Haney (FLH) Company is a family-owned and operated, Washington, DC-based financial services company that invests nationally in property development and real estate. FLH has holdings in several states and the District of Columbia. Since its founding in 1967 by Franklin Haney, FLH Company has acquired a portfolio worth over $10 billion, with a combined 15 million square feet of space. With its goal to build a better tomorrow for communities nationwide, FLH Company has become a leader in in the areas of creative planning, innovative financing, and acquisitions.  FLH Companyâs initial investments included development projects on hotels, apartments, parking garages, and office buildings located in the state of Tennessee, including the Internal Revenue Service Building located in Memphis. Other significant projects in the south included the Marietta Tower in downtown Atlanta, Georgia and the Social Security Payment Center in Birmingham, Alabama. FLH entered into food and beverage investments in the 1980s with the purchase of a Coca-Cola bottling company and a Miller beer distribution center.  Following its initial success in the southern region of the United States, FLH Company moved its operations to Washington, DC in 1994. With internal processes managed in Washington, DC by Frank Haney, Jr., FLH company is a frontrunning company in the Washington metropolitan area marketplace with the ownership of over 1 million square feet of space in the Portals Office Complex, home to the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) and an investment in the Dulles Greenway Toll Road in suburban Virginia of over $1 billion.  FLH Company currently has two headquarters, one located in Bethesda, Maryland, an immediate suburb of Washington, DC, and one in Chattanooga, Tennessee. The executive team is composed of chairman and founder, Frank Haney Sr., and his children, Frank Haney Jr. and Mae Haney Grennan, who serve as President and Chief Counsel.

Description: An inspirational brand with the mission to inspire and motivate people to live life without regret and accept challenges worth the risk.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: FÃ¼kitt is an inspirational brand with the mission to inspire and motivate people to live life without regret and accept challenges that are worth the risk. Everyone knows the concept of living life to the fullest but the problem is that it is simply human nature to take things for granted, which is why most people complain continuously about Mondays, traffic, and weather. People have argued that they can live life to the fullest every day but not only is that impossible, it is unhealthy. What do they do when they experience a tragic loss or disaster? The idea of living life to the fullest persuade us not to be bothered or influenced negatively by any situation, so we force ourselves into feeling happy, which often leads to abusing drugs and alcohol. Instead, we believe that we should embrace the pain to be able to appreciate the pleasure. Most of us don't need to be convinced to think more positively, we just simply need a reminder.  For example, how do you feel when a friend or relative passes away?  We all get a sense of gratitude for our lives and often decide to live life a little bit better, only because we appreciate our lives more. But this feeling is temporary so we all find ourselves complaining about situations again...until the next reminder, such as having a friend get into an accident, or seeing someone else less fortunate than you. Our goal is for our brand just to act as that reminder.  We're hoping that every time you wear our apparel and see our brand, you will be reminded to stop complaining about your life, to take life a little less for granted and to take more risks when it's worth it.
Industry Groups: Clothing and Apparel, Community and Lifestyle, Design, Health Care
